# Blog social & feature images

When creating or updating **Open Graph / LinkedIn / social preview** images for this blog:

1. **Do not** build one-off HTML under `/tmp` for production assets unless you are debugging. Prefer the repo pipeline.
2. Use **[scripts/social-image/README.md](scripts/social-image/README.md)** for colours, fonts, and dimensions.
3. Run from repo root (use `node scripts/social-image/capture.mjs` if `npm run` splits quoted args). For long titles, add **`--line4`** so the headline uses four shorter rows and stays clear of the avatar.
   ```bash
   node scripts/social-image/capture.mjs --out public/images/<slug>.png --line1 "..." --line2 "..." --line3 "..." [--line4 "..."]
   ```
4. Style changes belong in **[scripts/social-image/template.html](scripts/social-image/template.html)** so they are versioned (avatar horizontal inset: `.avatar-container` `right`; smaller = closer to the right edge).
5. In the post frontmatter, set **`socialImage`** to the public URL path (e.g. `'/images/<slug>.png'`) so **`BlogPost.astro`** passes it to **`BaseHead`** for Open Graph and Twitter.

Requires Playwright (`playwright` is a devDependency; install Chromium with `npx playwright install chromium` if capture fails).
